      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To ensure a 0% stockout rate, we need to calculate the order quantities using the Economic Order Quantity (EOQ) formula. \n\nFor Product A (Home Goods): \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * demand * lead time * standard deviation) \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * 500 * 2 * 50) \nEOQ = sqrt(10,000) \nEOQ ≈ 100 units\n\nFor Product B (Electronics): \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * demand * lead time * standard deviation) \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * 50 * 1 * 15) \nEOQ = sqrt(1500) \nEOQ ≈ 38.73 units (round up to 39 units)\n\nFor Product C (Groceries): \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * demand * lead time * standard deviation) \nEOQ = sqrt(2 * 2000 * 3 * 400) \nEOQ = sqrt(19,200,000) \nEOQ ≈ 1378.05 units (round up to 1379 units)\n\nThese are the exact order quantities to ensure a 0% stockout rate for each product.",
